				\begin{document}$$ d = \frac{k\lambda }{{\beta \cos (\theta_{o} )}} $$\end{document}where the value of d represents the size of the crystallites, and λ, θ0 and β are the wavelength of radiation, the Bragg diffraction angle and the intrinsic (true) profile full width at half maximum intensity (FWHM), respectively. The β parameter was calculated using the Gaussian–Gaussian relation (Tjong and Chen 2004):2β2=βexp2-βins2.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
