				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \beta^{2} = \beta_{\exp }^{2} - \beta_{\text{ins}}^{2} . $$\end{document}where βexp and βins are the FWHM of experimental and instrumental profiles, respectively. βexp and βins were determined by Gaussian curve fitting using a Matlab software. The annealed copper with average grain size of 5 μm was used as reference sample.
